function findNoOfInstructions(n, startPos, s) {
    const answer = Array(s.length).fill(0);
    let [x, y] = startPos;

    for (let i = 0; i < s.length; ++i) {
        let cnt = 0;
        let [cx, cy] = [x, y];
        for (let j = i; j < s.length; ++j) {
            const step = s[j];
            if (step === 'L') {
                if (cy === 0) break;
                cy -= 1;
            }
            else if (step === 'R') {
                if (cy === n - 1) break;
                cy += 1;
            }
            else if (step === 'U') {
                if (cx === 0) break;
                cx -= 1;
            }
            else {
                if (cx === n - 1) break;
                cx += 1;
            }
            cnt++;
            if (j === s.length - 1) break;
        }
        answer[i] = cnt;
    }

    return answer;
}
```


    Iterate through the string `s` considering each index as the starting point for execution. In each step, try executing instructions without going out of the grid boundary from that starting point.

In a nested loop, keep track of the robot position `cx` and `cy`, and for each step, check if the robot would go out-of-bounds on executing the instruction. If it goes out-of-bounds, break out of the loop for that starting point.

Finally, the count of instructions executed for each starting point is stored in the `answer` array.

